 :tx/rationale "AUDIT FINDING: DS2 group commit carries only runtime observation datoms (~10% of write traffic). Tool-level writes (braid_observe, braid_write, braid_task_go/close/create) still call live.write_tx() under the global write lock. The performance benefit of group commit (single fsync per batch, ~200us per write vs ~5ms for EDN serialize+fsync) is unrealized for the primary write workload. Root cause: MCP tool functions take &mut LiveStore and call write_tx internally. Fix requires either (a) refactoring tools to return TxFiles, or (b) read/write lock split so write tools still use write lock but reads use read lock. Option (b) is lower-risk and delivers 80% of the concurrency benefit. Traces to: INV-DAEMON-012, DS2, P99 write < 50ms target."
